### Exclude Files from Vitest Coverage Report

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/guide/coverage.md

Define patterns to exclude specific files from the coverage report, even if they match coverage.include, using the coverage.exclude option in vitest.config.ts.

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    coverage: {
      include: ['src/**/*.{ts,tsx}'],
      exclude: ['**/utils/users.ts']
    }
  }
})
```

--------------------------------

### Include Files in Vitest Coverage Report

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/guide/coverage.md

Specify which source files should be included in the coverage report by configuring the coverage.include option in vitest.config.ts.

```ts
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    coverage: {
      include: ['src/**/*.{ts,tsx}']
    }
  }
})
```

--------------------------------

### Ignore Entire File with v8

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/guide/coverage.md

Use `/* v8 ignore file -- @preserve */` at the top of a file to exclude its entire content from `v8` coverage reports.

```ts
/* v8 ignore file -- @preserve */
export function ignored() { // [!code error]
  return 'Whole file is ignored'// [!code error]
}// [!code error]
```

--------------------------------

### runTestSpecifications(specifications: TestSpecification[], allTestsRun = false): Promise<TestRunResult>

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/api/advanced/vitest.md

This method runs every test based on the received specifications. The second argument, `allTestsRun`, is used by the coverage provider to determine if it needs to include uncovered files in report.

```APIDOC
## runTestSpecifications

### Description
This method runs every test based on the received specifications. The second argument, `allTestsRun`, is used by the coverage provider to determine if it needs to include uncovered files in report. This method doesn't trigger `onWatcherRerun`, `onWatcherStart` and `onTestsRerun` callbacks. If you are rerunning tests based on the file change, consider using `rerunTestSpecifications` instead.

### Signature
```ts
function runTestSpecifications(
  specifications: TestSpecification[],
  allTestsRun = false
): Promise<TestRunResult>
```

### Parameters
#### Function Parameters
- **specifications** (TestSpecification[]) - Required - An array of test specifications to run.
- **allTestsRun** (boolean) - Optional - Defaults to `false`. Used by the coverage provider to determine if it needs to include uncovered files in the report.

### Response
#### Return Value
- **Promise<TestRunResult>** - A promise that resolves to the result of the test run.
```

--------------------------------

### Set 100% Coverage Threshold for Glob Patterns

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/config/coverage.md

Apply a 100% coverage threshold to files matching a specific glob pattern, simplifying the configuration for full coverage requirements.

```typescript
{
  coverage: {
    thresholds: {
      // Thresholds for all files
      functions: 95,
      branches: 70,

      // Thresholds for matching glob pattern
      'src/utils/**.ts': { 100: true },
      '**/math.ts': { 100: true }
    }
  }
}
```

--------------------------------

### Adjust Vitest Coverage Include Patterns for Precise Matching

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/guide/migration.md

Vitest's `coverage.include` and `exclude` patterns now match relative to the project root without `contains`, treating patterns without wildcards as directories.

```ts
export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    coverage: {
      include: ['src'],
    },
  },
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Custom Coverage Reporters

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/config/coverage.md

Shows how to integrate custom coverage reporters, either by referencing an NPM package or a local file path, with support for reporter-specific options.

```ts
{
    reporter: [
      // Specify reporter using name of the NPM package
      '@vitest/custom-coverage-reporter',
      ['@vitest/custom-coverage-reporter', { someOption: true }],

      // Specify reporter using local path
      '/absolute/path/to/custom-reporter.cjs',
      ['/absolute/path/to/custom-reporter.cjs', { someOption: true }]
    ]
  }
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Test File Inclusion

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/config/include.md

Explicitly define glob patterns for test files using the `include` option in `vitest.config.js`.

```js
import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config'

export default defineConfig({
  test: {
    include: [
      './test',
      './**/*.{test,spec}.ts(x)?',
    ],
  },
})
```

--------------------------------

### Configure Multiple Coverage Reporters with Options

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/config/coverage.md

Example demonstrating how to configure multiple coverage reporters, including passing specific options to individual reporters like `lcov` and `json`.

```ts
{
    reporter: [
      ['lcov', { 'projectRoot': './src' }],
      ['json', { 'file': 'coverage.json' }],
      ['text']
    ]
  }
```

--------------------------------

### Set Coverage Thresholds for Glob Patterns

Source: https://github.com/vitest-dev/vitest/blob/main/docs/config/coverage.md

Define specific coverage thresholds for files matching a glob pattern. Each pattern can also specify its own `perFile` setting, which is not inherited from the top-level configuration.

```typescript
{
  coverage: {
    thresholds: {
      // Thresholds for all files
      functions: 95,
      branches: 70,

      // Thresholds for matching glob pattern
      'src/utils/**.ts': {
        statements: 95,
        functions: 90,
        branches: 85,
        lines: 80,
        // each matching file must individually hit the thresholds above
        perFile: true,
      },

      // Files matching this pattern will only have lines thresholds set.
      // Global thresholds are not inherited.
      '**/math.ts': {
        lines: 100,
      }
    }
  }
}
```

